'''保罗·勒鲁瓦·罗伯逊'''（{{lang-en|Paul Leroy Robeson}}<ref name="Ford, Carin T. 2006 pg4">Ford 2006: 4</ref>，{{bd|1898年|4月9日|1976年|1月23日}}）是美国歌手、运动员、演员，因其在政治激进主义及在[[美国民权运动|美国民权运动]]中的活动而出名。<ref>{{cite news |title=From the Valley of Obscurity, Robeson's Baritone Rings Out; 22 Years After His Death, Actor-Activist Gets a Grammy |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1998/02/25/arts/valley-obscurity-robeson-s-baritone-rings-22-years-after-his-death-actor.html |quote=He was befriended by Jawaharlal Nehru, Noel Coward, Sergei Eisenstein, Jomo Kenyatta, Ernest Hemingway, James Joyce, Gertrude Stein and Emma Goldman. As a writer and performer, he was a pioneering human rights advocate, speaking out against segregation decades before the civil rights movement began and singing for American volunteers fighting in Spain against Franco and for struggling union members around the country. All this came at a time when discrimination against blacks was so entrenched, North and South, that Robeson was routinely forced to use freight elevators and denied entrance to hotels and restaurants. |work=The New York Times |date=February 25, 1998 |accessdate=2010-10-31 |archive-date=2020-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127213328/https://www.nytimes.com/1998/02/25/arts/valley-obscurity-robeson-s-baritone-rings-22-years-after-his-death-actor.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>罗伯逊是最早推广黑人福音乐的演唱歌手。他也是20世纪首位出演[[莎士比亚|莎士比亚]]戏剧《[[奧賽羅|奧賽羅]]》的黑人。<ref>Bogle 2001: 94</ref>在大学时期，他是一个出色的美式足球运动员，后来他成为了一个国际级的歌手，并从事剧院和电影的演出。他卷入了一系列政治事件如[[西班牙内战|西班牙内战]]，[[法西斯主义|法西斯主义]]和社会不公。他对于反帝国主义的呼吁，和[[共产主义|共产主义]]的关系，以及他对美国政府的批评导致他在[[麦卡锡主义|麦卡锡主义]]盛行的时代上了黑名单。健康原因迫使他退出了他的事业。直到晚年他仍然无悔于他所持的并不广为接受的政治立场。

